# v0.54 — Floating Damage Numbers

### New Files
- `scenes/ui/damage_number.tscn` + `scripts/damage_number.gd` — Floating damage/heal numbers
  - Spawns on hit, floats up, fades out over 0.9s
  - Random horizontal offset to prevent stacking
  - Red = damage, Green = heal, Gold = blocked (shield)
  - z_index=20 so it renders above units

### Updated
- `scripts/player.gd` — `show_damage_number()` on take_damage and merchant_heal
- `scripts/skeleton.gd` — `show_damage_number()` on take_damage
- `scripts/skeleton_captain.gd` — `show_damage_number()` on take_damage (skips if shield blocks)
- `scripts/skeleton_archer.gd` — `show_damage_number()` on take_damage
- Arrow projectile already calls `player.take_damage()`, numbers show automatically

### Visual Polish
- Damage numbers appear on all combatants: player, skeleton, captain, archer
- Player shows green heal numbers when merchant heals
- Shield block shows no damage number (gold flash = clear feedback)

### Zero Parse Errors ✅ (manual review)
